<lesson status="beta">

    <slide title="Views in a Nutshell" layout="normal">
        <div class="left">
            <b>#ViewsMatter</b>
            <p>Websites are judged, like it or not.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Content</li>
                <li>Structure and Navigation</li>
                <li>Visual Design</li>
                <li>Functionality</li>
                <li>Interactivity</li>
                <li>Innovation</li>
                <li>Overall Experience</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="right">
            <b>#LifeIsTooShort</b>
            <p>We're programmers, not designers.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Work with designers</li>
                <li>Agree on names for block element content</li>
                <li>Use view fragments to produce them</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </slide>

    <slide title="Construction &amp; Assembly" layout="normal">
        <div class="left">
            <b>Construction</b>
            <p>This refers to the creation of individual
                components (content) that go into a particular webpage.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Controller methods ... <code>$this->makeCarousel(...);</code>.</li>
                <li>Model methods ... <code>$this->gallery->makeCarousel(...);</code></li>
                <li>Library methods ... <code>$this->facebook->makeRecentPostsCarousel()</code>.
                </li>
                <li>These could even be delegated, for instance
                    <code>$data = file_get_contents(...);
                        $result = $this->parsedown->text($data);</code>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="right">
            <b>Assembly</b>
            <p>This refers to the arrangement, on page, of
                the components we have constructed.</p>
            <img class="scale" width="375" height="297" src="/pix/lessons/5/5-8.gif"/>     
        </div>

    </slide>


    <slide title="Is it Safe?" layout="normal"  tag="tag1">
        <p align="center">Aren't we working with CSS? What's XSS?<br/>
            <img class="scale" src="/pix/lessons/bob/exploits_of_a_mom.png"/>
        </p>
    </slide>

    <slide title="Who You Gonna Call?" layout="normal"  tag="tag1">
        <p align="center">Build them all, and tailor the CSS to arrange them properly.<br/>
